    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Clean, proportional fix for a real flaky test. The race analysis is accurate: `CreateChat` triggers async daemon processing, and reading `last_model_config_id` before the daemon commits gives nondeterministic results. Adding `testutil.Eventually` polls before editing and before asserting is the right approach, consistent with how this codebase synchronizes with async chat processing elsewhere.\n\nPariston traced all three orderings through the daemon's `persistStep` ownership guard (chatd.go ~7176-7187) and confirmed the production code is already safe; the flake was purely a test-timing issue. Takumi and Meruem independently verified the same. Multiple reviewers ran the test under `-race -count=N` with clean results.\n\nOne P3 about the polling condition shape, one nit.\n\n\"I came looking for a fight. Boring code. Correct fix.\" (Hisoka)\n\n> \ud83e\udd16 This review was automatically generated with Coder Agents.",
